Consider two graphs, Graph A and Graph B, which are shown below:

Graph A has vertices {1, 2, 3, 4, 5} and edges {(1, 2), (1, 3), (2, 3), (2, 4), (3, 5)}

Graph B has vertices {a, b, c, d, e} and edges {(a, b), (a, c), (a, e), (b, c), (c, d)}

Determine whether Graph A and Graph B are isomorphic. If they are, provide an isomorphism between the two graphs. If they are not, explain why not.
